CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 24, 1955, pg. 2, reads: "Heads United 'Y' Drive - Mrs. Homer S. Brown, left, and Dan C. Parrish, right, will lead the Centre Avenue Area team of the joint YMCA YWCA $5,000,000 building fund campaign. Mrs. brown is one of the vice presidents of the YWCA Metropolitan Board, and Mr. Parrish is vice president and treasurer of the Allegheny Asphalt and Paving Company."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Wilhelmina Byrd Brown wearing short sleeve dark leaf patterned dress, standing in interior with floral dish hung on wall and patterned curtains
